comments.body:
No, because then if you forward this from some other class, and it doesn't have a default, then I get a `null` for platform instead of a valid object if they don't provide a default. For instance:

```dart
class MyConfig extends Configuration {
  MyConfig({Platform platform}) : super(platform: platform);
}

void main() {
  MyConfiguration config = MyConfiguration(); // results in platform being set to null.
}
```

